    <Description>Cvent REST APIs: # Introduction<br/>
The Cvent API Platform is built around REST. We aim to provide intuitive endpoints that can be easily<br/>
discovered to help leverage the Cvent platform for your event needs. The RESTful APIs outlined here<br/>
use JSON-encoded request and response format, along with HTTP codes, to convey processing status of<br/>
requests received. The Cvent resources are protected using OAuth2.<br/>
<br/>
# Getting Started<br/>
<br/>
This SDK is generated by <a href="https://speakeasy.com">Speakeasy</a>. For usage instructions and code examples,<br/>
refer to the README and USAGE files included in this package. To obtain API credentials, visit the<br/>
<a href="https://developers.cvent.com/docs/rest-api/overview">Cvent REST API Overview</a>.<br/>
<br/>
The Cvent REST API uses <a href="https://oauth.net/2/">OAuth2</a> for authorization. The client credentials flow is supported.<br/>
Authorization code flow is only supported for planner users with the administrator role in Cvent.<br/>
<br/>
## Endpoints<br/>
<br/>
Endpoints start with `hostName` and `version`.<br/>
<br/>
The `hostname` will depend on the region that your Cvent account is hosted in:<br/>
<br/>
| Region        | Hostname                           |<br/>
|:--------------|:-----------------------------------|<br/>
| North America | https://api-platform.cvent.com     |<br/>
| Europe        | https://api-platform-eur.cvent.com |<br/>
<br/>
The current `version` of the Cvent API is `ea`.<br/>
<br/>
## Rate Limits<br/>
<br/>
Cvent APIs enforce rate limits to ensure platform stability. Your limits depend on your tier: Free,<br/>
Standard, or Premium.<br/>
<br/>
### Usage Tiers<br/>
<br/>
| Tier     | Daily Calls | Calls per Second | Max Burst |<br/>
| -------- | ----------- | ---------------- | --------- |<br/>
| Free     | 1,000       | 2                | 1         |<br/>
| Standard | 15,000      | 10               | 10        |<br/>
| Premium  | 500,000     | 25               | 25        |<br/>
<br/>
- **Daily calls** define how many requests you can make in a 24-hour period. Quota resets at 12 midnight (+0 GMT).<br/>
- **Calls per second** define how many requests you can make in a 1-second window.<br/>
- **Max Burst** defines how many requests you can make at once.<br/>
<br/>
Check your tier via <a href="#operation/getUsageTier">Get Current Usage Tier</a>. These limits may change as the platform evolves.<br/>
<br/>
### Handling Rate Limits<br/>
<br/>
When you exceed rate limits, the API returns `429 Too Many Requests`. Implement exponential backoff<br/>
to handle these errors gracefully. For per-second limits, start with a 2 second wait plus random<br/>
milliseconds, doubling the wait time for each retry up to 16 seconds. For daily quota limits,<br/>
wait until after 12 midnight UTC.<br/>
<br/>
## Filtering<br/>
<br/>
Use filters to narrow down results. The filter follows the pattern<br/>
`filter=&apos;field&apos; comparisonType &apos;value&apos;`. The value can be enclosed with single quotes (&apos;) or double quotes (&quot;).<br/>
<br/>
```bash<br/>
GET {hostName}/{version}/contacts?filter=lastName eq &apos;Smith&apos;<br/>
```<br/>
<br/>
To pass a single quote in the filter&apos;s value, use double quotes around the string.<br/>
<br/>
```bash<br/>
GET {hostName}/{version}/contacts?filter=lastName eq &quot;O&apos;Keenan&quot;<br/>
```<br/>
<br/>
To pass a double quote, use double quotes around the string and escape each inner quote with `\`.<br/>
<br/>
```bash<br/>
GET {hostName}/{version}/events?filter=eventName eq &quot;\&quot;Yearly\&quot; Conference&quot;<br/>
```<br/>
<br/>
## Versioning<br/>
<br/>
We track both backward-compatible and backward-incompatible changes.<br/>
<br/>
**Backward compatible:** Adding new resources, optional parameters, or attributes; changing format (not type) of IDs; increasing string field lengths.<br/>
<br/>
**Backward incompatible:** Adding required parameters; deleting resources or attributes; changing data types. When breaking changes occur, a new API version is released while the old version remains available temporarily.<br/>
<br/>
For documentation and guides, visit <a href="https://developers.cvent.com">developers.cvent.com</a>.<br/>
